Weather Forecast is a Java Application that accepts the cityName from user and prints out the 5day/3hour data, 16day/daily data and graph comparing temperatures. This is all done by clicking a single "go" button. Each output is defined as a seperate thread. The data is displayed in different tabs. The UI is designed using Java Swing.

Below are the steps to set up the project:

Steps to Start Mongo Server:

1. After installing MongoDB and Mongo-java-driver-3.8.0.jar, create database and log directories.
Command- md "\data\db" "\data\log"

2. Start MongoDB database
"C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\4.0\bin\mongod.exe" --dbpath="c:\data\db"

3. In another command prompt, connect to MongoDB
"C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\4.0\bin\mongo.exe"

Steps to run the Application:

1. To run this weather application, we need the following jar files:
json-simple-1.1.jar
jcommon-1.0.23.jar
jfreechart-1.0.19.jar
mongo-java-driver-3.8.0.jar

2. To add all these jars to your project's class path, right click on the project, go to properties -> libraries. Click on "Add JAR/Folder" and select the required jar files.

3. Run WeatherInfo.java file to run the application.


